  "notes": [
    "UC Santa Cruz students may choose to complete one or more minors, provided they can finish all required coursework within their maximum enrollment terms and allowable credits. While a minor will appear on a student's official transcript, it will not be listed on their diploma. Pursuing a minor is a personal decision that should align with a student's educational and career goals. Students do not apply for minors when submitting their application to UC Santa Cruz. After enrolling, transfer students interested in pursuing a minor should contact the department offering the minor for guidance.",
    "Prior to July 1, 2023, UC Santa Cruz's General Chemistry series was offered as Chemistry 1A, 1B and 1C, with associated laboratories Chemistry 1M and 1N. Starting in the 2023-2024 academic year, this series was replaced by two new distinct series: Chemistry 3A, 3B and 3C, with labs Chemistry 3BL and 3CL; and Chemistry 4A and 4B with labs Chemistry 4AL and 4BL. Prospective transfer students who started working toward the Chemistry 1 series prior to the 2024-2025 academic year may complete equivalent courses as originally approved, and their articulated coursework will fulfill the General Chemistry series requirement for this minor.",
    "Prospective transfer students interested in minoring in biology are encouraged to complete the following courses, or their articulated equivalents, prior to transferring: BIOL 20A \u2013 Cell and Molecular Biology BIOL 20L \u2013 Experimental Biology Laboratory BIOL 20L is not required for students who have completed BIOL 20A and BIOE 20B articulated equivalents at California Community Colleges. BIOE 20B \u2013 Development and Physiology General Chemistry series See \"General Chemistry Series\" below for important information CHEM 8A \u2013 Organic Chemistry CHEM 8B \u2013 Organic Chemistry Refer to the \u201cPreparation for the Minor\u201d section below for courses approved to apply to each of the requirements listed above. It is strongly recommended that community college students complete all General Chemistry coursework at one institution prior to transfer to UC Santa Cruz. Please visit the Molecular, Cell and Developmental Biology (MCD) website to learn more about this minor."
  ]
